1
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,640
Will. Why is this happening?

2
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:28,480
I don't know.  You look beautiful.

3
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:32,370
I think it's bad luck for the groom to see the bride before the wedding.

4
00:02:32,370 --> 00:02:35,490
Make way. Let me through!  How dare you!

5
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:40,140
Stand your men down at once! Do you hear me?

6
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:43,430
Governor Weatherby Swann, it's been too long.

7
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,230
Cutler Beckett?

8
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:48,020
It's Lord now. Actually.

9
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:53,620
Lord or not, you have no reason and no authority to arrest this man.

10
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:58,700
In fact, I do. Mr. Mercer?

11
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:03,530
The warrant for the arrest of one William Turner.

12
00:03:06,990 --> 00:03:09,320
This warrant is for Elizabeth Swann!

13
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,560
Oh, is it? That's annoying, my mistake...  Arrest her.

14
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,380
- On what charges?!
- No!

15
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:22,770
Aha, here's the one for William Turner.  And I have another one for a Mr. James Norrington. Is he present?

16
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:24,070
What are the charges?

17
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:27,850
Commodore Norrington resigned his commission some months ago.

18
00:03:27,850 --> 00:03:30,590
I don't believe that was the answer to the question I asked.

19
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:34,010
Lord Beckett, in the category of questions not answered -

20
00:03:34,010 --> 00:03:40,190
We are under the jurisdiction of the King's governor of Port Royal and you will tell us what we are charged with.

21
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:47,730
The charge... is conspiring to set free a man convicted of crimes against the Crown and Empire

22
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:51,610
and condemned to death for which the...

23
00:03:51,610 --> 00:03:57,310
For which the punishment, regrettably, is also death.

24
00:03:57,310 --> 00:04:00,620
Perhaps you remember a certain pirate named Jack Sparrow.

25
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:03,630
Captain!

26
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:06,300
Captain Jack Sparrow.

27
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:13,710
Captain Jack Sparrow. Yes, I thought you might.

28
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:18,770
50 men on a dead man's chest.

29
00:04:18,770 --> 00:04:23,940
Yo ho ho and a bottle of rum.

30
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:29,450
Drink and the devil had done (??) for the rest.

31
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:35,790
Yo ho ho and a bottle of rum.

32
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,490
Sorry, mate.

33
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:41,340
Do you mind if we make a little side trip?

34
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:45,010
I didn't think so.

35
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:53,170
Not quite according to plan.

36
00:06:53,170 --> 00:06:57,590
Complications arose, ensued, were overcome.

37
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,990
You got what you went in for, then?

38
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:01,480
Muhuh.

39
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:07,390
Captain, I think the crew - meaning me, as well -

40
00:07:07,390 --> 00:07:10,870
were expecting something a bit more...  shiny.

41
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:15,170
What with the Isla de Muerta going all pear-shapes, reclaimed by the sea and the treasure with it.

42
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:18,050
And the Royal Navy chasing us all around the Atlantic.

43
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:20,540
And the hurricane!

44
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:27,420
All in all, it seems some time since we did a speck of honest pirating.

45
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:28,920
Shiny?

46
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,560
Aye, shiny.

47
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:38,470
Is that how you're all feeling, then? Perhaps dear ol' Jack is not serving your best interests as Captain?

48
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,250
Awk, walk the plank.

49
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,900
What did the bird say?!

50
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:47,880
Do not blame the bird. Show us, what is on that piece of cloth there.

51
00:07:55,820 --> 00:07:57,190
You know that don't do no good.

52
00:07:57,190 --> 00:08:01,180
It does me.

53
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,500
It's a key.

54
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:08,770
No, much more better! It is a drawing of a key.

55
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:19,200
Gentlemen, what do keys do?

56
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:24,560
Keys... unlock things?

57
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,810
And whatever this key unlocks, inside there's something valuable.

58
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:31,320
So, we're setting out to find whatever this key unlocks!

59
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:37,380
No. We don't have the key, we can't open whatever it is we don't have that it unlocks.

60
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:42,270
So, what purpose would be served in finding whatever need be unlocked, which we don't have,

61
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:46,020
without first having found the key what unlocks it.

62
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:49,140
So, we're going after this key!

63
00:08:49,140 --> 00:08:54,130
You're not making any sense at all. Any more questions?

64
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:56,900
So... Do we have a heading?

65
00:08:56,900 --> 00:09:00,860
Ah!  A heading.

66
00:09:00,860 --> 00:09:04,060
Set sail in a...

67
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,160
general...

68
00:09:10,470 --> 00:09:12,570
that way direction!

69
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:13,770
Captain?

70
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:18,550
Come on. Snap to and make sail, you know how this works. Oi, oi!

71
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:24,110
I've notice lately,

72
00:09:24,110 --> 00:09:28,920
the Captain seem to be acting a bit strange...er.

73
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,750
Setting sail without knowing his own heading,

74
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:39,390
something's got Jack vexed. You mark my words, what bodes ill for Jack Sparrow, bodes ill for us all.

75
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:55,500
Lord Beckett, the prisoner as ordered, sir.

76
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,390
Those won't be necessary.

77
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:05,250
The East India Trading Company has need of your services.

78
00:10:09,860 --> 00:10:16,520
We wish for you to act as our agent in a business transaction with our mutual friend - Captain Sparrow.

79
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,710
More acquaintance than friend. How do you know him?

80
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:21,110
We've had dealings in the past.

81
00:10:22,290 --> 00:10:26,240
And we've each left our mark on the other.

82
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,540
What mark did he leave on you?

83
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:34,810
By your efforts, Jack Sparrow was set free.

84
00:10:34,810 --> 00:10:40,310
I would like you to go to him and recover a certain property in his possession.

85
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:44,960
Recover. At the point of a sword?

86
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,370
Bargain.

87
00:10:52,930 --> 00:10:56,190
Letters of Marque.

88
00:10:56,190 --> 00:11:04,300
You will offer what amounts to a full pardon - Jack will be free, a privateer in the employ of England.

89
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:08,780
Somehow I doubt Jack will consider employment the same as being free.

90
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:11,600
Freedom.

91
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:15,100
Jack Sparrow is a dying breed.

92
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:20,400
The world is shrinking. The blank edges of the map filled in.

93
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:24,700
Jack must find his place in the New World or perish.

94
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:26,810
Not unlike you, Mr. Turner.

95
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:30,840
You and your fianc? face the hangman's noose.

96
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:34,610
So you get both Jack and the Black Pearl.

97
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:36,430
The Black Pearl?

98
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:37,860
The property you want that he possesses.

99
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,900
A ship? Hardly.

100
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:44,090
The item in question is considerably smaller and far more valuable.

101
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:47,310
??

102
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:50,450
a compass?

103
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:53,320
Ah, you know it.

104
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:57,960
Bring back that compass, or there's no deal.

105
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,230
Why is the rum always gone?

106
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:35,370
Oh... that's why.

107
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:21,300
Time's run out, Jack.

108
00:13:39,050 --> 00:13:43,120
Bootstrap. Bill Turner?

109
00:13:48,210 --> 00:13:50,010
You look good, Jack.

110
00:13:57,210 --> 00:13:59,280
Is this a dream?

111
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:01,100
No.

112
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:04,960
I thought not, if it were, there'd be rum.

113
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:15,310
You got the Pearl back, I see.

114
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:20,100
I had some help retrieving the Pearl, by the way.

115
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,750
Your son.

116
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:25,940
William?

117
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:29,210
Ended up pirate after all.

118
00:14:29,210 --> 00:14:33,280
And to what do I owe the pleasure of your carbuncle?

119
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:36,500
He sent me.

120
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:39,600
Davy Jones.

121
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:44,250
Ah. So it's you, then.

122
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:49,000
He shanghaied you into service, eh?

123
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,950
I chose it.

124
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:54,840
I'm sorry for the part I played in the mutiny against you, Jack.

125
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:59,090
I stood up for ya.

126
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:01,660
Everything went wrong after that.

127
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:09,310
They strapped me to a cannon, I ended up on the bottom of the ocean,

128
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:11,930
the weight of the water crushing down on me.

129
00:15:11,930 --> 00:15:15,070
Unable to move,

130
00:15:15,070 --> 00:15:17,670
unable to die, Jack,

131
00:15:17,670 --> 00:15:23,850
and I thought that even the tiniest hope of escaping this fate, I would take it.

132
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:26,110
I would trade anything for it.

133
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:31,300
It's funny what a man will do to forestall his final judgment.

134
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,810
You made a deal with him, too, Jack.

135
00:15:33,810 --> 00:15:38,750
He raised the Pearl from the depths for you, thirteen years you've been Captain.

136
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:39,950
Technically, I -

137
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:43,090
Jack. Won't be able to talk yourself out of this.

138
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:46,150
The terms would apply to me, apply to you, as well.

139
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:50,830
One soul, bound to crew a hundred years upon his ship.

140
00:15:50,830 --> 00:15:53,320
Yes, but The Flying Dutchman already has a Captain, so there's really -

141
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,070
Then it's the Locker for you!

142
00:15:55,070 --> 00:15:58,260
Though this is terrible, the leviathan will find you

143
00:15:58,260 --> 00:16:02,240
and drag the Pearl back to the depths and you along with it.

144
00:16:03,850 --> 00:16:09,430
Any idea when Jones might release said terrible beastie?

145
00:16:09,430 --> 00:16:12,830
I already told you, Jack.

146
00:16:12,830 --> 00:16:16,170
The time is up.

147
00:16:16,170 --> 00:16:22,220
It comes now.(??)

148
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,180
the black spot.

149
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:38,430
On deck all hands! Make faster -- gasket! On deck! Scurry!

150
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:43,090
Scurry on! Move it! Move it!! I want movement!

151
00:16:43,090 --> 00:16:45,010
Mr. Skinner, pick it up! (??)

152
00:16:45,010 --> 00:16:48,700
I want a --- (??), plenty running.

153
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,970
Run as if the devil himself and itself was upon us!

154
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:51,970
Do we have a heading?

155
00:16:51,970 --> 00:16:53,170
Ah!

156
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,910
Rum! Land.

157
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:59,240
Ah!

158
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,090
Which port?

159
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:03,320
I didn't say port. I said land, any land.  Ah!

160
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:11,840
Jack's hat! Steer about!

161
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,860
No, no, leave it.

162
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:16,910
Rum.

163
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,650
Back to your stations, the lot of ya!

164
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:30,730
Jack?

165
00:17:30,730 --> 00:17:32,280
Shh!

166
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:36,050
For the love of Mother and Child, Jack, what's coming after us?

167
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,610
Nothing.

168
00:18:51,410 --> 00:18:53,170
You're not... you can't be here.

169
00:18:53,170 --> 00:18:55,660
I think you'll find he can.

170
00:18:55,660 --> 00:18:57,290
Mr. Swann.

171
00:18:57,290 --> 00:19:02,710
Governor Swann, still. Do you think I wear this wig to keep my head warm?

172
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:06,250
Jack's compass? What does Beckett want with that?

173
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:12,820
Doesn't matter. I'm to find Jack and convince him to return to Port Royal and in exchange the charges against us will be dropped.

174
00:19:12,820 --> 00:19:16,680
No, we must find our own avenue to secure your freedom.

175
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:19,370
Is that a lack of faith in Jack... or in me?

176
00:19:19,370 --> 00:19:25,780
You would risk your life to save Sparrow's does not mean that he would do the same for anyone else.

177
00:19:25,780 --> 00:19:27,190
Now,

178
00:19:27,190 --> 00:19:29,520
where's that dog with the keys?

179
00:19:30,530 --> 00:19:34,530
I have faith in you. Both of you.

180
00:19:36,930 --> 00:19:39,690
Where will you find him?

181
00:19:39,690 --> 00:19:41,630
Tortuga.

182
00:19:41,630 --> 00:19:44,690
I'll start there and I won't stop searching 'till I find him.

183
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:48,470
And then I intend to return here to marry you.

184
00:19:48,470 --> 00:19:49,810
Properly?

185
00:19:49,810 --> 00:19:53,030
With your leave, if you'll still have me.

186
00:19:53,030 --> 00:19:55,720
If it weren't for these bars, I'd have you already.

187
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:04,630
I'll wait for you.

188
00:20:04,630 --> 00:20:07,450
Keep a weather eye on the horizon.

189
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:20,000
Captain Jack Sparrow?

190
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,110
Hadn't been thought about,

191
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,790
heard he was dead.

192
00:20:24,790 --> 00:20:28,440
Singapore, that's what I heard. Drunk, with a smile on his face.

193
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:31,270
Sure as a tide, Jack Sparrow,

194
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:33,550
turned up in Singapore.

195
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,900
Jack Sparrow?

196
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,780
I haven't seen him in a month.

197
00:20:36,780 --> 00:20:39,860
When you find him, you give him a message.

198
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,570
Can't say about Jack Sparrow,

199
00:20:44,570 --> 00:20:50,170
but this island just south of the straits where I trade spice for...

200
00:20:50,170 --> 00:20:53,530
delicious,long pork.

201
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:57,990
Cannot say about Jack. But you'll find that ship there.

202
00:20:57,990 --> 00:21:00,110
A ship with black sails.

203
00:21:07,290 --> 00:21:09,620
My brother will take you ashore.

204
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,340
What's wrong, the beach is right there?

205
00:21:21,340 --> 00:21:22,800
Ne bougeais pas, c'set beaucoup trop dangereaux.

206
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:23,440
What?

207
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:28,010
Je ne pois, c'est trop dangereaux, j'avais le dit.  Bon voyage, monsieur.

208
00:21:28,010 --> 00:21:29,230
Bon voyage, monsieur.

209
00:21:54,470 --> 00:21:58,940
Jack! Jack Sparrow!

210
00:22:04,820 --> 00:22:07,850
Marty!

211
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:10,080
Cotton!

212
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,780
Anybody?

213
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:19,820
Ah, a familiar face.

214
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:22,020
Awk, don't eat me!

215
00:22:22,020 --> 00:22:23,500
I'm not going to eat you.

216
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:27,900
Don't eat me. Don't eat me. Awk!

217
00:22:38,530 --> 00:22:39,630
Gibbs.

218
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:13,620
Come on! Let's go!

219
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:16,170
Come on!!

220
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:18,020
who wants it?!

221
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:21,810
I can do this all day!

222
00:24:25,660 --> 00:24:29,780
Jack? Jack Sparrow.

223
00:24:29,780 --> 00:24:33,400
I can honestly say I'm glad to see you.

224
00:24:40,630 --> 00:24:43,960
Jack, it's me, Will Turner!

225
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:52,410
Tell them to let me down.

226
00:25:12,340 --> 00:25:17,250
Jack, the compass, that's all I need. Elizabeth is in danger. We were arrested for trying to help you.

227
00:25:17,250 --> 00:25:19,710
She faces the gallows!

228
00:25:31,150 --> 00:25:34,970
Maliki liki! Maliki liki!(??????)

229
00:25:34,970 --> 00:25:37,380
Save me.

230
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:42,050
Jack, what did you tell them? No!

231
00:25:42,050 --> 00:25:45,280
What about Elizabeth?

232
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:48,840
Jaaack!

233
00:25:57,750 --> 00:25:59,240
Come quickly.

234
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:01,840
You've got to tell me what's happening.

235
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:07,090
I may still have some standing in the keep. I've arranged passage to England. The Captain is a friend of mine.

236
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:09,190
No! Will's gone to find Jack!

237
00:26:09,190 --> 00:26:12,420
We cannot count on William Turner. Come!

238
00:26:12,420 --> 00:26:14,050
He's a better man than you give him credit for.

239
00:26:14,050 --> 00:26:18,560
Of course, this is no time for innocence. Beckett has offered one pardon only. One!

240
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:22,240
And that is promised to Jack Sparrow. Even if Will succeeds...

241
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:27,310
you're not asking me to endure the sight of my daughter walking to the gallows. Do not.

242
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:33,090
Perhaps, I can ensure a fair trial for Will, if he returns.

243
00:26:33,090 --> 00:26:35,650
A fair trial for Will ends in a hanging.

244
00:26:35,650 --> 00:26:38,360
Then there is nothing left for you here.

245
00:26:44,950 --> 00:26:46,160
Wait inside.

246
00:26:47,820 --> 00:26:49,280
Captain?

247
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:54,660
Captain..

248
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:04,460
Evening, Gov'ner.  Shame, huh?

249
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:09,410
He was carrying this  It's a letter to the King.

250
00:27:09,410 --> 00:27:11,210
It's from you.

251
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:16,570
Ah...  Elizabeth.

252
00:27:18,140 --> 00:27:19,750
What are you doing?!

253
00:27:23,060 --> 00:27:24,270
Where is she?

254
00:27:24,270 --> 00:27:25,940
Who?

255
00:27:42,970 --> 00:27:50,260
No doubt you've discovered that loyalty is no longer the currency of the realm as your father believes.

256
00:27:50,260 --> 00:27:52,840
Then what is?

257
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:56,570
I'm afraid currency is the currency of the realm.

258
00:27:56,570 --> 00:28:00,540
