494
00:55:02,870 --> 00:55:05,910
If you don't want it, give it back.

495
00:55:05,910 --> 00:55:07,820
No.

496
00:55:07,820 --> 00:55:11,500
Then it helps.

497
00:55:11,500 --> 00:55:16,610
It seems... we have a need to find the Flying Dutchman.

498
00:55:19,570 --> 00:55:23,650
A touch...  of destiny.

499
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:40,320
That's the Flying Dutchman?

500
00:55:42,650 --> 00:55:44,370
She doesn't look like much.

501
00:55:44,370 --> 00:55:49,510
Neither do you... do not underestimate it.

502
00:55:49,510 --> 00:55:51,110
Must've run afoul of the reef.

503
00:55:51,110 --> 00:55:53,660
What's your plan?

504
00:55:53,660 --> 00:55:57,150
I row over, search the ship until I find your bloody key.

505
00:55:57,150 --> 00:55:59,620
And if there are crewmen?

506
00:55:59,620 --> 00:56:02,620
I cut down anyone in my path.

507
00:56:02,620 --> 00:56:05,830
I like it. Simple, easy to remember.

508
00:56:05,830 --> 00:56:09,220
Your chariot awaits you. Ahahaha!

509
00:56:46,690 --> 00:56:50,020
Go on your whereabouts and pray.

510
00:57:04,580 --> 00:57:07,330
Get back! Back!

511
00:57:38,960 --> 00:57:42,220
Five men still alive, the rest have moved on.

512
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:04,230
Do you fear death?

513
00:58:04,230 --> 00:58:10,840
Do you fear that dark abyss?

514
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:19,260
All your deeds laid bare. All your sins punished.

515
00:58:19,260 --> 00:58:24,000
I can offer you an escape.

516
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:26,490
Don't listen to him!

517
00:58:35,700 --> 00:58:41,000
Do you not fear death?

518
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,760
I'll take my chances, sir.

519
00:58:43,760 --> 00:58:45,150
To the depths.

520
00:58:51,350 --> 00:58:53,740
Cold blood!

521
00:58:53,740 --> 00:59:02,990
Life is cruel. Why should the afterlife be any different? I offer you a choice.

522
00:59:02,990 --> 00:59:09,360
Join my crew and postpone the judgment.

523
00:59:09,360 --> 00:59:15,380
One hundred years before the mast.

524
00:59:15,380 --> 00:59:19,470
Will ye serve?

525
00:59:19,470 --> 00:59:21,150
I-I-I will serve.

526
00:59:21,150 --> 00:59:23,540
That-a.

527
00:59:29,970 --> 00:59:35,090
You are neither dead nor dying. What is your purpose here?

528
00:59:38,930 --> 00:59:42,980
Jack Sparrow sent me to settle his debt.

529
00:59:42,980 --> 00:59:46,330
What is your purpose here?

530
00:59:46,330 --> 00:59:52,060
Jack Sparrow... sent me to settle his debt.

531
00:59:52,060 --> 01:00:00,640
Ha. Did he now? I'm sorely tempted to accept that offer.

532
01:00:15,030 --> 01:00:23,450
You have a debt to pay. You've been Captain of the Black Pearl for thirteen years. That was our agreement.

533
01:00:23,450 --> 01:00:27,270
Technically, I was only Captain for two years, then I was viciously mutinied upon.

534
01:00:27,270 --> 01:00:33,090
Then you were a poor Captain, but a Captain nonetheless. Have you not introduced yourself

535
01:00:33,090 --> 01:00:39,810
all these years as 'Captain Jack Sparrow'?

536
01:00:39,810 --> 01:00:42,800
Yeah, I gave you payment. One soul to serve on your ship is already over there.

537
01:00:42,800 --> 01:00:45,990
One soul is not equal to another.

538
01:00:45,990 --> 01:00:50,230
Aha! So we've establish my proposal is sound in principle, now we're just haggling over price.

539
01:00:52,600 --> 01:00:53,580
Price?

540
01:00:57,450 --> 01:01:00,580
Just how many souls, do you think, my soul is worth?

541
01:01:04,380 --> 01:01:10,110
One hundred souls. Three days.

542
01:01:10,110 --> 01:01:13,670
You're a darling, mate. Send me back the boy, I'll get started right off.

543
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:22,770
I keep the boy, a good, faith payment. That leaves you only ninety-nine to go. Haha, haha.

544
01:01:22,770 --> 01:01:29,990
Have you not met Will Turner? He's noble, heroic, a terrific soprano. Worth at least four,

545
01:01:29,990 --> 01:01:36,080
maybe three and a half..And did I happen to mention...

546
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:47,520
he's in love. With a girl. Due to be married. Betrothed.

547
01:01:47,520 --> 01:01:57,370
Dividing him from her and her from him would only be half as cruel as actually allowing them to be joined in holy matrimony. Aye?

548
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:05,510
I keep the boy. Ninty-nine souls-ah.

549
01:02:05,510 --> 01:02:08,550
But I wonder, Sparrow...

550
01:02:08,550 --> 01:02:20,040
can you live with this? Can you condemn an innocent man - a friend - to a lifetime of servitude in your name while you roam free?

551
01:02:23,150 --> 01:02:28,280
Yep. I'm good with it. Shall we seal it in blood, I mean, uh, ink?

552
01:02:32,850 --> 01:02:34,640
Three days-ah.

553
01:02:39,940 --> 01:02:41,900
Three days.

554
01:02:50,110 --> 01:02:51,060
Uh, Mr. Gibbs?

555
01:02:51,060 --> 01:02:52,750
Aye.

556
01:02:52,750 --> 01:02:55,110
I feel sullied and unusual.

557
01:02:55,110 --> 01:03:00,670
And how do we intend to harvest these ninety-nine souls in three days?

558
01:03:00,670 --> 01:03:05,860
Fortunately, he was mum as the condition in which these souls need be.

559
01:03:05,860 --> 01:03:09,640
Aah, Tortuga.

560
01:03:09,640 --> 01:03:11,540
Tortuga.

561
01:03:15,150 --> 01:03:21,920
It's an outrage. Port Tariff's buried (??) in fees, war handling and, heaven help us, pilotage.

562
01:03:21,920 --> 01:03:26,420
Are we all to work for these India Trading Company, then?

563
01:03:26,420 --> 01:03:31,020
I'm afraid, sir... Tortuga is the only free post left in these waters.

564
01:03:31,020 --> 01:03:38,270
A pirate port is what you mean. Well, I'm sorry, an honest sailor is what I am and make my living fair and I sleep well each night, thank you.

565
01:03:40,050 --> 01:03:41,090
Sir!

566
01:04:04,460 --> 01:04:07,240
She wants you to do something.

567
01:04:10,310 --> 01:04:11,790
She's trying to give a sign.

568
01:04:28,480 --> 01:04:32,030
Look, there! There it is! There's the sign.

569
01:04:32,030 --> 01:04:33,620
I seen it.

570
01:04:33,620 --> 01:04:36,560
So we can be saved. Looks like entrails.

571
01:04:36,560 --> 01:04:37,880
That'd be a bad sign.

572
01:04:37,880 --> 01:04:39,350
What's that over there?

573
01:04:59,480 --> 01:05:02,860
And what makes you think you're worthy to crew the Black Pearl?

574
01:05:02,860 --> 01:05:08,060
Truth be told, I never sailed a day in me life. I figure I should get out and see the world while I'm still young.

575
01:05:08,060 --> 01:05:11,850
You'll do. Make your mark.  Next!

576
01:05:11,850 --> 01:05:21,580
My wife run off with my dog, and I'm drunk for a month, and I don't give an ass rat's if I live or die.

577
01:05:21,580 --> 01:05:24,630
Perfect! Next!

578
01:05:24,630 --> 01:05:26,960
Me have one arm and a bum leg.

579
01:05:26,960 --> 01:05:28,710
It's the crow's nest for you.

580
01:05:28,710 --> 01:05:29,760
I know what I want.

581
01:05:29,760 --> 01:05:30,790
Next!

582
01:05:30,790 --> 01:05:36,440
Ever since I was little, I've always wanted to sail the seas. Forever.

583
01:05:36,440 --> 01:05:39,140
Sooner than you think. Sign the roster.

584
01:05:39,140 --> 01:05:41,380
Thanks very much.

585
01:05:41,380 --> 01:05:42,810
How are we going?

586
01:05:42,810 --> 01:05:46,870
Including those four? That gives us... four.

587
01:05:49,960 --> 01:05:52,720
And what's your story?

588
01:05:52,720 --> 01:05:54,910
My story?

589
01:05:54,910 --> 01:05:59,700
It's exactly the same as your story, just one chapter behind.

590
01:05:59,700 --> 01:06:11,150
I chased a man across the seven seas. (??)and my life.

591
01:06:16,070 --> 01:06:17,190
Commodore?

592
01:06:17,190 --> 01:06:19,610
No, not anymore, weren't you listening?

593
01:06:23,830 --> 01:06:31,830
I nearly had you all off Tripoli. I would've, if not for the hurricane.

594
01:06:31,830 --> 01:06:35,160
Lord. You didn't try to sail through it?

595
01:06:35,160 --> 01:06:40,710
So do I make your crew or not?

596
01:06:40,710 --> 01:06:43,400
You haven't said where you're going.

597
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:46,520
Somewhere nice!

598
01:06:46,520 --> 01:06:51,490
So am I worthy to serve under Captain Jack Sparrow?

599
01:06:51,490 --> 01:06:56,490
Or should I just kill you now?

600
01:07:03,680 --> 01:07:06,080
You're hired.

601
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:09,380
Sorry. Old habits and all that.

602
01:07:09,380 --> 01:07:10,930
Easy sailor!

603
01:07:26,070 --> 01:07:27,220
Time to go.

604
01:07:27,220 --> 01:07:27,950
Aye.

605
01:08:11,990 --> 01:08:13,040
Thanks, mate.

606
01:08:19,640 --> 01:08:20,800
Carry on.

607
01:08:28,710 --> 01:08:36,500
Come on, then! Who wants some? For my lordly line, I'll have you one by one. Come on, who's first?

608
01:08:39,800 --> 01:08:42,330
I just wanted the pleasure of doing that myself.

609
01:09:09,780 --> 01:09:15,020
James Norrington.  What has the world done to you?

610
01:09:43,830 --> 01:09:52,410
Heave! Heave! Heave!

611
01:10:00,450 --> 01:10:04,050
Secure the mast, man called Mr. Turner.

612
01:10:07,310 --> 01:10:08,750
Secure it!

613
01:10:14,650 --> 01:10:17,200
- Step aside!
- mind yourself!

614
01:10:17,200 --> 01:10:19,360
Hey! Let go, boy!

615
01:10:32,570 --> 01:10:35,220
Haul that weasel to his feet.

616
01:10:40,630 --> 01:10:44,270
Five lashes are in my due. To stay honor.

617
01:10:44,270 --> 01:10:45,710
No.

618
01:10:45,710 --> 01:10:51,870
Impeding me in my duties? You'll share the punishment.

619
01:10:51,870 --> 01:10:53,290
I'll take it all.

620
01:10:53,290 --> 01:11:00,990
Will you now? And what would prompt such an act of charity?

621
01:11:04,430 --> 01:11:05,340
My son.

622
01:11:11,290 --> 01:11:12,460
He's my son.

623
01:11:24,560 --> 01:11:31,990
What fortuitous circumstance be this. Five lashes be owed, I believe it is.

624
01:11:37,900 --> 01:11:39,360
No. No, I won't!

625
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:47,900
The cat's out of the bag, Mr. Turner. Your issue will feel its sting be it at the Bo'sun's hand or your own.

626
01:11:51,250 --> 01:11:53,830
No.

627
01:11:53,830 --> 01:11:55,700
- Bo'sun!
- No!

628
01:12:39,210 --> 01:12:42,780
You've had it easy boy.

629
01:12:42,780 --> 01:12:43,920
Will!

630
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:45,790
I don't need your help.

631
01:12:47,410 --> 01:12:53,850
The Bo'sun prides himself on cleaving flesh from bone with every swing.

632
01:12:53,850 --> 01:12:58,910
So I'm to understand what you did was an act of compassion.

633
01:12:58,910 --> 01:13:00,190
Yes.

634
01:13:06,490 --> 01:13:17,730
One hundred years before the mast. Loosing who you are, bit by bit.
'Till you end up, end up like poor, Wyvern, here.

635
01:13:17,730 --> 01:13:25,130
Once you've sworn an oath to the Dutchman, there's no leaving it. 
Not until your debt is paid.

636
01:13:25,130 --> 01:13:26,770
I've sworn no oath.

637
01:13:29,250 --> 01:13:32,880
Then you must get away.

638
01:13:32,880 --> 01:13:35,940
Not until I find this.

639
01:13:35,940 --> 01:13:37,870
The key.

640
01:13:45,360 --> 01:13:48,990
The Dead Man's Chest.

641
01:13:48,990 --> 01:13:51,080
What do you know of it?

642
01:13:51,080 --> 01:13:58,540
Open the chest with the key and stab the heart. No, don't stab the heart.

643
01:13:58,540 --> 01:14:08,410
The Dutchman needs a living heart or there'll be no captain. If there's no captain, there's no one to have the key.

644
01:14:08,410 --> 01:14:12,030
So the Captain has the key.

645
01:14:12,030 --> 01:14:14,030
Where is the key?

646
01:14:14,030 --> 01:14:15,180
Hidden.

647
01:14:15,180 --> 01:14:16,750
Where is the chest.

648
01:14:16,750 --> 01:14:21,070
Hidden.

649
01:14:21,070 --> 01:14:22,970
Captain Sparrow?

650
01:14:22,970 --> 01:14:25,490
Come to join me crew, lad? Welcome aboard.

651
01:14:25,490 --> 01:14:29,040
I'm here to find the man I love.

652
01:14:29,040 --> 01:14:32,320
I'm deeply flattered, son, but my first and only love is the sea.

653
01:14:34,770 --> 01:14:38,830
Meaning William Turner, Captain Sparrow.

654
01:14:38,830 --> 01:14:42,460
Elizabeth?  Hide the rum.

655
01:14:42,460 --> 01:14:47,680
You know these clothes do not flatter you at all. It should be a dress or nothing. I happen to have no dress in my cabin.

656
01:14:47,680 --> 01:14:50,720
Jack.

657
01:14:50,720 --> 01:14:54,220
I know Will came to find you, where is he?

658
01:14:54,220 --> 01:15:04,320
Darling, I am truly unhappy to have to tell you this, but through an unfortunate and entirely unforeseeable series of circumstances that had nothing whatsoever to do with me,

659
01:15:04,320 --> 01:15:15,320
poor Will has been press-ganged into Davy Jones's crew.

